              <th class="font-display text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink py-4 pr-4">Pop-Up Ball</th>
              <th class="font-display text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink py-4 pr-4">Right-Angle Chain</th>
              <th class="font-display text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink py-4 pr-4">Turntable</th>
              <th class="font-display text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink py-4">Push Diverter</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-base text-ink-muted">
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink">Max Load</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">300 lbs</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">75 lbs</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">4,000 lbs</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">10,000 lbs</td>
              <td class="py-3 font-mono text-sm">100 lbs</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink">Cycle Time</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">2-4 sec</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">3-5 sec</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">3-5 sec</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">6-10 sec</td>
              <td class="py-3 font-mono text-sm">1-2 sec</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink">Product Orientation</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Maintained</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Maintained</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Maintained</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Rotated</td>
              <td class="py-3">May rotate</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink">Direction Angles</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">90&deg; only</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Any angle</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">90&deg; only</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Any angle</td>
              <td class="py-3">90&deg; typical</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink">Best For</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Cases, cartons</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Light items, multi-dir</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Heavy pallets</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Very heavy loads</td>
              <td class="py-3">Rejects, light divert</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink">Relative Cost</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">$$$</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">$$</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">$$$</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">$$$$</td>
              <td class="py-3 font-mono text-sm">$$</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mt-4">Cycle times and load ratings represent typical values from Hytrol, Dematic, and Intelligrated product lines. See <a href="/resources/conveyor-cost-guide/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">cost guide</a> for pricing factors.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Applications -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface" aria-labelledby="apps-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Applications</div>
      <h2 id="apps-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        Transfer Conveyor <span class="text-accent">Applications</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p><strong class="text-ink">Packaging line routing:</strong> <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Packaging lines</a> use transfers to route products between parallel process lines. Cases divert from a main transport line to one of several case packers, labelers, or palletizers using pop-up chain transfers. The PLC routes each case based on product SKU, destination, or load-balancing logic.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Pallet handling:</strong> <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/pallet/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Pallet conveyor systems</a> use right-angle chain transfers and turntables to route loaded pallets between stretch wrappers, labelers, and shipping lanes. The heavy loads (2,000-4,000 lbs) require positive chain drive or turntable rotation. <a href="/conveyor-types/cdlr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">CDLR conveyors</a> feed right-angle chain transfers for heavy pallet routing.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Distribution center sortation:</strong> Transfer conveyors divert totes and cartons from trunk lines to pick zones, pack stations, and shipping lanes. High-volume operations use high-speed shoe sorters or pop-up wheel diverters (300-600 FPM). Lower-volume operations use pop-up chain transfers or push diverters.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Reject and quality control:</strong> <a href="/conveyor-functions/reject-systems/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Reject systems</a> use push diverters to remove failed products from the main conveyor line. Checkweighers, metal detectors, and vision systems trigger the diverter to push rejects onto a spur conveyor or into a reject bin. Push diverters offer the fastest cycle time (1-2 seconds) for reject applications.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink"><a href="/conveyor-functions/collating-laning/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Collating and laning:</a></strong> Transfer conveyors distribute products from a single infeed lane across multiple output lanes. Each transfer diverts a programmed number of products to fill lanes evenly before <a href="/conveyor-functions/tray-loading/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">tray loading</a> or case packing.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Vertical integration:</strong> Transfer conveyors connect horizontal conveyor runs to <a href="/conveyor-types/vertical-reciprocating/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">vertical reciprocating conveyors (VRCs)</a> and spiral conveyors. A right-angle transfer feeds product onto the VRC platform or spiral infeed, and another transfer receives product at the upper level.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Selection Criteria -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim bg-dots" aria-labelledby="selection-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Selection Guide</div>
      <h2 id="selection-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        How to Select a <span class="text-accent">Transfer Conveyor</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p><strong class="text-ink">Product weight drives the first cut.</strong> Products under 100 lbs qualify for pop-up chains, pop-up balls, or push diverters. Products from 100-500 lbs need pop-up chain or right-angle chain transfers. Products over 500 lbs require right-angle chain transfers or turntables. <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/pallet/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Pallet loads</a> over 2,000 lbs typically use turntables or heavy-duty right-angle chain transfers.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Throughput determines cycle time requirements.</strong> Calculate the maximum number of transfers per minute needed. Divide 60 seconds by the required transfers per minute to get the maximum allowable cycle time. Pop-up chains at 2-4 seconds deliver 15-30 transfers per minute. Turntables at 6-10 seconds deliver 6-10 transfers per minute. If throughput exceeds single-transfer capacity, add parallel transfers or switch to high-speed sortation technology.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Orientation sensitivity matters.</strong> Push diverters can rotate products during the push. Pop-up chain transfers and right-angle transfers maintain product orientation. Turntables intentionally rotate the product. If barcode labels, product graphics, or downstream equipment require a specific product orientation, avoid push diverters.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Direction flexibility.</strong> Pop-up chains and right-angle transfers handle 90-degree transfers only. Pop-up ball transfers and turntables handle any angle. Push diverters typically push at 90 degrees but angled sweeps can push at 30-60 degrees.</p>

        <p>Transfers must integrate with upstream <a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">accumulation zones</a> that meter products into the transfer at the correct spacing and timing. <a href="/conveyor-types/mdr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">MDR conveyor zones</a> upstream of the transfer provide precise product positioning for reliable transfer operation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide mb-10">
        Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8" open>
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is a transfer conveyor?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
            <p>A transfer conveyor changes product direction between two conveyor lines, typically at 90 degrees. Types include pop-up chain, pop-up ball, right-angle chain, turntable, and push diverter. See our <a href="/conveyor-types/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">complete conveyor type guide</a> for the full picture.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is the difference between a pop-up transfer and a push diverter?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
            <p>Pop-up transfers lift chains or balls above the roller surface to carry the product sideways. Push diverters physically push the product off the line. Pop-ups maintain orientation and handle higher loads. Push diverters are cheaper and faster but may rotate the product.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How fast can a transfer conveyor operate?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
            <p>Pop-up chain: 30-120 FPM, 2-4 sec cycle. Push diverter: up to 200 FPM, 1-2 sec cycle. Turntable: 6-10 sec cycle. High-speed sortation diverters handle 300-600 FPM. Choose based on your transfers-per-minute requirement.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-ink-light" aria-labelledby="related-heading">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent-bright mb-4">Related Pages</div>
      <h2 id="related-heading" class="font-display text-3xl font-extrabold text-white tracking-wide mb-8">Continue <span class="text-accent-bright">Researching</span></h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
        <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/" class="p-5 border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] hover:bg-white/[0.06] hover:border-accent/40 transition-all group">
          <div class="font-display text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-white group-hover:text-accent-bright transition-colors mb-1">Roller Conveyors</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/60">Transport lines that feed transfers</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="p-5 border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] hover:bg-white/[0.06] hover:border-accent/40 transition-all group">
          <div class="font-display text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-white group-hover:text-accent-bright transition-colors mb-1">Accumulation</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/60">Buffer before transfer points</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/conveyor-types/cdlr-conveyors/" class="p-5 border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] hover:bg-white/[0.06] hover:border-accent/40 transition-all group">
          <div class="font-display text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-white group-hover:text-accent-bright transition-colors mb-1">CDLR Conveyors</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/60">Heavy-duty pallet transfer feed</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/conveyor-functions/reject-systems/" class="p-5 border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] hover:bg-white/[0.06] hover:border-accent/40 transition-all group">
          <div class="font-display text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-white group-hover:text-accent-bright transition-colors mb-1">Reject Systems</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/60">Push diverter applications</p>
        </a>
